.SH "NAME"
pci_sriov_set_totalvfs \- \- reduce the TotalVFs available
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ pci_sriov_set_totalvfs('u
.BI "int pci_sriov_set_totalvfs(struct\ pci_dev\ *\ " "dev" ", u16\ " "numvfs" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
the PCI PF device
.RE
.PP
\fInumvfs\fR
.RS 4
number that should be used for TotalVFs supported
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Should be called from PF driver\*(Aqs probe routine with device\*(Aqs mutex held\&.
.PP
Returns 0 if PF is an SRIOV\-capable device and value of numvfs valid\&. If not a PF return \-ENOSYS; if numvfs is invalid return \-EINVAL; if VFs already enabled, return \-EBUSY\&.
